10. Quick Implementation Checklist
• Match the review depth to the real use case. A note-taking bot is not a decision engine; do not
treat them the same.
• Make sure procurement, legal, security, and the business owner see the same final
recommendation, not four contradictory folk tales.
• Tie approved vendors back to the AI use case registry so vendor review and use case approval
stay connected.
• Re-run the review when the vendor adds major AI features, changes data use terms, or expands
into higher-risk use cases.
